
[1]slippery

   SLIP'PERY, a.

   1. Smooth; glib; having the quality opposite to adhesiveness; as, oily
   substances render things slippery.

   2. Not affording firm footing or confidence; as a slippery promise. The
   slipp'ry tops of human state.

   3. Not easily held; liable or apt to slip away. The slipp'ry god will
   try to loose his hold.

   4. Not standing firm, as slippery standers.

   5. Unstable; changeable; mutable; uncertain; as the slippery state of
   kings.

   6. Not certain in its effect; as a slippery trick.

   7. Lubrious; wanton; unchaste.
